				<name type="primary" sortindex="3" value="A Formidable Enemy: Rules for Miniature Skirmishes in The French &amp; Indian War" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>A Formidable Enemy is a fast-paced skirmish game set in the French &amp;amp; Indian War. There are two PDF downloads included with your purchase: a 36 page rulebook, and a 45 page book of army lists and rosters. You can use one of the six premade armies, or create your own force with a comprehensive point system. The game has a historical &amp;quot;feel&amp;quot; through the use of Assets specific to different types of characters &amp;amp; units. Optional &amp;quot;otherworldly&amp;quot; rules are included to take advantage of some of the outstanding figures available for this period. Color photographs of figures from Conquest Miniatures, Eureka Miniatures, AW Miniatures, &amp;amp; Warlord Games, as well as structures by Acheson Creations (all used with permission) illustrate both documents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Part One contains the game rules (summarized in a 4-page Quick Reference), Assets to personalize your troops (Abilities &amp;amp; Characteristics, Weapons, Artillery, Special Unit Members, Equipment, Vehicles, Animals, &amp;amp; Structures), Liabilities, Otherworldly Assets (including Divine Interventions), Templates, Markers &amp;amp; Tokens, &amp;amp; optional Event Cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Part Two contains brief historical information, Army Lists, and Unit Cards for the Indians, French, British, Canadians, &amp;amp; American Colonials. There is also information on Bears, Dogs, Zombyes, &amp;amp; a few other optional (but fun!) non-historical additions to the game (inspired mainly by figures from Conquest Miniatures). There are six sample armies, &amp;amp; information about how to create your own troops &amp;amp; armies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
